{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"5e2ecbfa-4677-46a9-8778-330bc5ea6a0f","content":"**The issue is that \"scoped\" means something different in MAUI than in ASP.NET Core.**\n\nIn ASP.NET Core, a new DI scope is created **per HTTP request**, so `AddScoped<MyDbContext>()` gives you a fresh instance for each request.\n\nIn MAUI, **there is no per-request scope**. The app creates a single root scope at startup that lives for the entire application lifetime. This makes `AddScoped` behave essentially like `AddSingleton` — your `DbContext` is reused across all navigations, accumulating tracked entities and stale data.\n\n### Fix\n\nUse `AddTransient` so a new `DbContext` is created each time it's injected:\n\n```csharp\nbuilder.Services.AddTransient<MyDbContext>();\n```\n\nOr, for more control, inject `IServiceScopeFactory` and create explicit scopes:\n\n```csharp\nusing var scope = scopeFactory.CreateScope();\nvar db = scope.ServiceProvider.GetRequiredService<MyDbContext>();\n```\n\n**TL;DR:** MAUI has one scope for the app's lifetime. `AddScoped` ≈ `AddSingleton` there. Switch to `AddTransient` or manage scopes manually.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b3f71a83-b8e4-4c63-8929-217e27482ba7","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about a common pitfall when moving from ASP.NET Core to .NET MAUI regarding dependency injection scoping — specifically why `AddScoped` behaves differently in MAUI than in ASP.NET Core.\n\nThis is a conceptual question I can answer directly without needing to search any codebase.\n\nThe key issue: In ASP.NET Core, a \"scope\" is created per HTTP request, so `AddScoped` gives you a new instance per request. In MAUI, there's no concept of an HTTP request — the app has a single scope for its entire lifetime. So `AddScoped` effectively behaves like `AddSingleton`, meaning your DbContext is reused across all page navigations, and its change tracker accumulates stale data.","outputTokens":483,"requestId":"3C26:16C73:DB8190:110D886:6A012BE7"},"id":"8656b9fd-4f8e-4029-9a27-ae0920f54a8d","timestamp":"2026-05-11T01:08:02.545Z","parentId":"f5be5e2e-eb0d-4c39-ad32-f0a44cce6053"}
